ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_ax-bnd | |- ( A. z z = x \/ ( A. z z = y \/ A. x A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) ) |
| 2 |  | #P_ax-4--i | |- ( A. x A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) -> A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) |
| 3 | 2 | #P_orim2i | |- ( ( A. z z = y \/ A. x A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) -> ( A. z z = y \/ A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_orim2i | |- ( ( A. z z = x \/ ( A. z z = y \/ A. x A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) ) -> ( A. z z = x \/ ( A. z z = y \/ A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) ) ) |
| 5 | 1, 4 | #P_ax-mp | |- ( A. z z = x \/ ( A. z z = y \/ A. z ( x = y -> A. z x = y ) ) ) |
\
 Proof that ~ ax-i12 follows from ~ ax-bnd .  So that we can track which theorems rely on ~ ax-bnd , proofs should reference ~ ax-i12 rather than this theorem.  (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 17-Aug-2018.)  (New usage is discouraged).  (Proof modification is discouraged.)
